1. RESOLVED — Spreadsheet import for restock management.
   The spreadsheet import was removed from the New Restock Request flow and moved into Supplier Management's Bulk Link Items modal, where staff can upload CSV/TSV rows, map columns, and create/link many inventory or non-inventory supplier products to one or more suppliers in one operation.

2. RESOLVED — Restock request history tab.
   Request History now excludes `linked_to_po` requests, keeps active linked requests in Current Requests, groups history by supplier, and opens a supplier-history modal containing that supplier's received/cancelled requests.

3. RESOLVED — Merge duplicate PO items for multiple requests on the same PO.
   Scheduled/request-queue PO generation and automatic request attachment merge duplicate product/type/unit-cost lines into one purchase-order line. Receiving and unlinking logic now operates through all restock items attached to the merged PO line.

4. RESOLVED — Modal-based details for PO, current requests, supplier management, and upcoming schedules.
   The current request modal now mirrors the request detail information more closely and exposes request cancellation for open requested requests.

5. RESOLVED — Distinguish scheduled vs manual POs.
   Manual POs no longer auto-link current requests and now support adding linked supplier products directly to the manual PO during creation.

6. RESOLVED — Pharmacist/admin dashboard navigation focus.
   The missing `/admin/more` destination now exists as a server-rendered admin directory of navigation cards to all admin workspaces.
